3591
3592static void maybePrintCallAddrSpace(const Value *Operand, const Instruction *I,
3593 raw_ostream &Out) {
3594 // We print the address space of the call if it is non-zero.
3595 unsigned CallAddrSpace = Operand->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
3596 bool PrintAddrSpace = CallAddrSpace != 0;
3597
3598 if (!PrintAddrSpace) {
3599 const Module *Mod = getModuleFromVal(I);
3600 // We also print it if it is zero but not equal to the program address space
3601 // or if we can't find a valid Module* to make it possible to parse
3602 // the resulting file even without a datalayout string.
3603 if (!Mod || Mod->getDataLayout().getProgramAddressSpace() != 0)
3604 PrintAddrSpace = true;
3605 }
3606
3607 // Hack for CHERI: don't print the addrspace() attribute for capability calls
3608 // FIXME: this hack should be removed once all testcases have been updated
3609 if (PrintAddrSpace) {
3610 // if it is a CHERI cap call, don't print the AS
3611 if (isCheriPointer(CallAddrSpace, getDataLayoutOrNull(I)))
3612 PrintAddrSpace = false;
3613 if (CallAddrSpace == 0) {
3614 // Also don't print an address space for legacy ABI:
3615 // FIXME: remove once we drop legacy ABI completely
3616 const DataLayout* DL = getDataLayoutOrNull(I);
3617 assert(DL && "Should only reach this branch if DL != null");
3618 if (isCheriPointer(DL->getProgramAddressSpace(), DL))
3619 PrintAddrSpace = false;
3620 }
3621 }
3622 if (PrintAddrSpace)
3623 Out << " addrspace(" << CallAddrSpace << ")";
3624}
3625
3626// This member is called for each Instruction in a function..
3627void AssemblyWriter::printInstruction(const Instruction &I) {
3628 if (AnnotationWriter) AnnotationWriter->emitInstructionAnnot(&I, Out);
3629
3630 // Print out indentation for an instruction.
3631 Out << " ";
3632
3633 // Print out name if it exists...
3634 if (I.hasName()) {
3635 PrintLLVMName(Out, &I);
3636 Out << " = ";
3637 } else if (!I.getType()->isVoidTy()) {
3638 // Print out the def slot taken.
3639 int SlotNum = Machine.getLocalSlot(&I);
3640 if (SlotNum == -1)
3641 Out << "<badref> = ";
3642 else
3643 Out << '%' << SlotNum << " = ";
3644 }
3645
3646 if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I)) {
3647 if (CI->isMustTailCall())
3648 Out << "musttail ";
3649 else if (CI->isTailCall())
3650 Out << "tail ";
3651 else if (CI->isNoTailCall())
3652 Out << "notail ";
3653 }
3654
3655 // Print out the opcode...
3656 Out << I.getOpcodeName();
3657
3658 // If this is an atomic load or store, print out the atomic marker.
3659 if ((isa<LoadInst>(I) && cast<LoadInst>(I).isAtomic()) ||
3660 (isa<StoreInst>(I) && cast<StoreInst>(I).isAtomic()))
3661 Out << " atomic";
3662
3663 if (isa<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I) && cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I).isWeak())
3664 Out << " weak";
3665
3666 // If this is a volatile operation, print out the volatile marker.
3667 if ((isa<LoadInst>(I) && cast<LoadInst>(I).isVolatile()) ||
3668 (isa<StoreInst>(I) && cast<StoreInst>(I).isVolatile()) ||
3669 (isa<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I) && cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I).isVolatile()) ||
3670 (isa<AtomicRMWInst>(I) && cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I).isVolatile()))
3671 Out << " volatile";
3672
3673 // Print out optimization information.
3674 WriteOptimizationInfo(Out, &I);
3675
3676 // Print out the compare instruction predicates
3677 if (const CmpInst *CI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(&I))
3678 Out << ' ' << CmpInst::getPredicateName(CI->getPredicate());
3679
3680 // Print out the atomicrmw operation
3681 if (const AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(&I))
3682 Out << ' ' << AtomicRMWInst::getOperationName(RMWI->getOperation());
3683
3684 // Print out the type of the operands...
3685 const Value *Operand = I.getNumOperands() ? I.getOperand(0) : nullptr;
3686
3687 // Special case conditional branches to swizzle the condition out to the front
3688 if (isa<BranchInst>(I) && cast<BranchInst>(I).isConditional()) {
3689 const BranchInst &BI(cast<BranchInst>(I));
3690 Out << ' ';
3691 writeOperand(BI.getCondition(), true);
3692 Out << ", ";
3693 writeOperand(BI.getSuccessor(0), true);
3694 Out << ", ";
3695 writeOperand(BI.getSuccessor(1), true);
3696
3697 } else if (isa<SwitchInst>(I)) {
3698 const SwitchInst& SI(cast<SwitchInst>(I));
3699 // Special case switch instruction to get formatting nice and correct.
3700 Out << ' ';
3701 writeOperand(SI.getCondition(), true);
3702 Out << ", ";
3703 writeOperand(SI.getDefaultDest(), true);
3704 Out << " [";
3705 for (auto Case : SI.cases()) {
3706 Out << "\n ";
3707 writeOperand(Case.getCaseValue(), true);
3708 Out << ", ";
3709 writeOperand(Case.getCaseSuccessor(), true);
3710 }
3711 Out << "\n ]";
3712 } else if (isa<IndirectBrInst>(I)) {
3713 // Special case indirectbr instruction to get formatting nice and correct.
3714 Out << ' ';
3715 writeOperand(Operand, true);
3716 Out << ", [";
3717
3718 for (unsigned i = 1, e = I.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
3719 if (i != 1)
3720 Out << ", ";
3721 writeOperand(I.getOperand(i), true);
3722 }
3723 Out << ']';
3724 } else if (const PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(&I)) {
3725 Out << ' ';
3726 TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
3727 Out << ' ';
3728
3729 for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); op < Eop; ++op) {
3730 if (op) Out << ", ";
3731 Out << "[ ";
3732 writeOperand(PN->getIncomingValue(op), false); Out << ", ";
3733 writeOperand(PN->getIncomingBlock(op), false); Out << " ]";
3734 }
3735 } else if (const ExtractValueInst *EVI = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(&I)) {
3736 Out << ' ';
3737 writeOperand(I.getOperand(0), true);
3738 for (const unsigned *i = EVI->idx_begin(), *e = EVI->idx_end(); i != e; ++i)
3739 Out << ", " << *i;
3740 } else if (const InsertValueInst *IVI = dyn_cast<InsertValueInst>(&I)) {
3741 Out << ' ';
3742 writeOperand(I.getOperand(0), true); Out << ", ";
3743 writeOperand(I.getOperand(1), true);
3744 for (const unsigned *i = IVI->idx_begin(), *e = IVI->idx_end(); i != e; ++i)
3745 Out << ", " << *i;
3746 } else if (const LandingPadInst *LPI = dyn_cast<LandingPadInst>(&I)) {
3747 Out << ' ';
3748 TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
3749 if (LPI->isCleanup() || LPI->getNumClauses() != 0)
3750 Out << '\n';
3751
3752 if (LPI->isCleanup())
3753 Out << " cleanup";
3754
3755 for (unsigned i = 0, e = LPI->getNumClauses(); i != e; ++i) {
3756 if (i != 0 || LPI->isCleanup()) Out << "\n";
3757 if (LPI->isCatch(i))
3758 Out << " catch ";
3759 else
3760 Out << " filter ";
3761
3762 writeOperand(LPI->getClause(i), true);
3763 }
3764 } else if (const auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(&I)) {
3765 Out << " within ";
3766 writeOperand(CatchSwitch->getParentPad(), /*PrintType=*/false);
3767 Out << " [";
3768 unsigned Op = 0;
3769 for (const BasicBlock *PadBB : CatchSwitch->handlers()) {
3770 if (Op > 0)
3771 Out << ", ";
3772 writeOperand(PadBB, /*PrintType=*/true);
3773 ++Op;
3774 }
3775 Out << "] unwind ";
3776 if (const BasicBlock *UnwindDest = CatchSwitch->getUnwindDest())
3777 writeOperand(UnwindDest, /*PrintType=*/true);
3778 else
3779 Out << "to caller";
3780 } else if (const auto *FPI = dyn_cast<FuncletPadInst>(&I)) {
3781 Out << " within ";
3782 writeOperand(FPI->getParentPad(), /*PrintType=*/false);
3783 Out << " [";
3784 for (unsigned Op = 0, NumOps = FPI->getNumArgOperands(); Op < NumOps;
3785 ++Op) {
3786 if (Op > 0)
3787 Out << ", ";
3788 writeOperand(FPI->getArgOperand(Op), /*PrintType=*/true);
3789 }
3790 Out << ']';
3791 } else if (isa<ReturnInst>(I) && !Operand) {
3792 Out << " void";
3793 } else if (const auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CatchReturnInst>(&I)) {
3794 Out << " from ";
3795 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(0), /*PrintType=*/false);
3796
3797 Out << " to ";
3798 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(1), /*PrintType=*/true);
3799 } else if (const auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(&I)) {
3800 Out << " from ";
3801 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(0), /*PrintType=*/false);
3802
3803 Out << " unwind ";
3804 if (CRI->hasUnwindDest())
3805 writeOperand(CRI->getOperand(1), /*PrintType=*/true);
3806 else
3807 Out << "to caller";
3808 } else if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I)) {
3809 // Print the calling convention being used.
3810 if (CI->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) {
3811 Out << " ";
3812 PrintCallingConv(CI->getCallingConv(), Out);
3813 }
3814
3815 Operand = CI->getCalledValue();
3816 FunctionType *FTy = CI->getFunctionType();
3817 Type *RetTy = FTy->getReturnType();
3818 const AttributeList &PAL = CI->getAttributes();
3819
3820 if (PAL.hasAttributes(AttributeList::ReturnIndex))
3821 Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
3822
3823 // Only print addrspace(N) if necessary:
3824 maybePrintCallAddrSpace(Operand, &I, Out);
3825
3826 // If possible, print out the short form of the call instruction. We can
3827 // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function,
3828 // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function.
3829 //
3830 Out << ' ';
3831 TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out);
3832 Out << ' ';
3833 writeOperand(Operand, false);
3834 Out << '(';
3835 for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = CI->getNumArgOperands(); op < Eop; ++op) {
3836 if (op > 0)
3837 Out << ", ";
3838 writeParamOperand(CI->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttributes(op));
3839 }
3840
3841 // Emit an ellipsis if this is a musttail call in a vararg function. This
3842 // is only to aid readability, musttail calls forward varargs by default.
3843 if (CI->isMustTailCall() && CI->getParent() &&
3844 CI->getParent()->getParent() &&
3845 CI->getParent()->getParent()->isVarArg())
3846 Out << ", ...";
3847
3848 Out << ')';
3849 if (PAL.hasAttributes(AttributeList::FunctionIndex))
3850 Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttributes());
3851
3852 writeOperandBundles(CI);
3853 } else if (const InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(&I)) {
3854 Operand = II->getCalledValue();
3855 FunctionType *FTy = II->getFunctionType();
3856 Type *RetTy = FTy->getReturnType();
3857 const AttributeList &PAL = II->getAttributes();
3858
3859 // Print the calling convention being used.
3860 if (II->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) {
3861 Out << " ";
3862 PrintCallingConv(II->getCallingConv(), Out);
3863 }
3864
3865 if (PAL.hasAttributes(AttributeList::ReturnIndex))
3866 Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
3867
3868 // Only print addrspace(N) if necessary:
3869 maybePrintCallAddrSpace(Operand, &I, Out);
3870
3871 // If possible, print out the short form of the invoke instruction. We can
3872 // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function,
3873 // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function.
3874 //
3875 Out << ' ';
3876 TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out);
3877 Out << ' ';
3878 writeOperand(Operand, false);
3879 Out << '(';
3880 for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = II->getNumArgOperands(); op < Eop; ++op) {
3881 if (op)
3882 Out << ", ";
3883 writeParamOperand(II->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttributes(op));
3884 }
3885
3886 Out << ')';
3887 if (PAL.hasAttributes(AttributeList::FunctionIndex))
3888 Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttributes());
3889
3890 writeOperandBundles(II);
3891
3892 Out << "\n to ";
3893 writeOperand(II->getNormalDest(), true);
3894 Out << " unwind ";
3895 writeOperand(II->getUnwindDest(), true);
3896 } else if (const CallBrInst *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(&I)) {
3897 Operand = CBI->getCalledValue();
3898 FunctionType *FTy = CBI->getFunctionType();
3899 Type *RetTy = FTy->getReturnType();
3900 const AttributeList &PAL = CBI->getAttributes();
3901
3902 // Print the calling convention being used.
3903 if (CBI->getCallingConv() != CallingConv::C) {
3904 Out << " ";
3905 PrintCallingConv(CBI->getCallingConv(), Out);
3906 }
3907
3908 if (PAL.hasAttributes(AttributeList::ReturnIndex))
3909 Out << ' ' << PAL.getAsString(AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
3910
3911 // If possible, print out the short form of the callbr instruction. We can
3912 // only do this if the first argument is a pointer to a nonvararg function,
3913 // and if the return type is not a pointer to a function.
3914 //
3915 Out << ' ';
3916 TypePrinter.print(FTy->isVarArg() ? FTy : RetTy, Out);
3917 Out << ' ';
3918 writeOperand(Operand, false);
3919 Out << '(';
3920 for (unsigned op = 0, Eop = CBI->getNumArgOperands(); op < Eop; ++op) {
3921 if (op)
3922 Out << ", ";
3923 writeParamOperand(CBI->getArgOperand(op), PAL.getParamAttributes(op));
3924 }
3925
3926 Out << ')';
3927 if (PAL.hasAttributes(AttributeList::FunctionIndex))
3928 Out << " #" << Machine.getAttributeGroupSlot(PAL.getFnAttributes());
3929
3930 writeOperandBundles(CBI);
3931
3932 Out << "\n to ";
3933 writeOperand(CBI->getDefaultDest(), true);
3934 Out << " [";
3935 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CBI->getNumIndirectDests(); i != e; ++i) {
3936 if (i != 0)
3937 Out << ", ";
3938 writeOperand(CBI->getIndirectDest(i), true);
3939 }
3940 Out << ']';
3941 } else if (const AllocaInst *AI = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(&I)) {
3942 Out << ' ';
3943 if (AI->isUsedWithInAlloca())
3944 Out << "inalloca ";
3945 if (AI->isSwiftError())
3946 Out << "swifterror ";
3947 TypePrinter.print(AI->getAllocatedType(), Out);
3948
3949 // Explicitly write the array size if the code is broken, if it's an array
3950 // allocation, or if the type is not canonical for scalar allocations. The
3951 // latter case prevents the type from mutating when round-tripping through
3952 // assembly.
3953 if (!AI->getArraySize() || AI->isArrayAllocation() ||
3954 !AI->getArraySize()->getType()->isIntegerTy(32)) {
3955 Out << ", ";
3956 writeOperand(AI->getArraySize(), true);
3957 }
3958 if (AI->getAlignment()) {
3959 Out << ", align " << AI->getAlignment();
3960 }
3961
3962 unsigned AddrSpace = AI->getType()->getAddressSpace();
3963 if (AddrSpace != 0) {
3964 Out << ", addrspace(" << AddrSpace << ')';
3965 }
3966 } else if (isa<CastInst>(I)) {
3967 if (Operand) {
3968 Out << ' ';
3969 writeOperand(Operand, true); // Work with broken code
3970 }
3971 Out << " to ";
3972 TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
3973 } else if (isa<VAArgInst>(I)) {
3974 if (Operand) {
3975 Out << ' ';
3976 writeOperand(Operand, true); // Work with broken code
3977 }
3978 Out << ", ";
3979 TypePrinter.print(I.getType(), Out);
3980 } else if (Operand) { // Print the normal way.
3981 if (const auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(&I)) {
3982 Out << ' ';
3983 TypePrinter.print(GEP->getSourceElementType(), Out);
3984 Out << ',';
3985 } else if (const auto *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(&I)) {
3986 Out << ' ';
3987 TypePrinter.print(LI->getType(), Out);
3988 Out << ',';
3989 }
3990
3991 // PrintAllTypes - Instructions who have operands of all the same type
3992 // omit the type from all but the first operand. If the instruction has
3993 // different type operands (for example br), then they are all printed.
3994 bool PrintAllTypes = false;
3995 Type *TheType = Operand->getType();
3996
3997 // Select, Store and ShuffleVector always print all types.
3998 if (isa<SelectInst>(I) || isa<StoreInst>(I) || isa<ShuffleVectorInst>(I)
3999 || isa<ReturnInst>(I)) {
4000 PrintAllTypes = true;
4001 } else {
4002 for (unsigned i = 1, E = I.getNumOperands(); i != E; ++i) {
4003 Operand = I.getOperand(i);
4004 // note that Operand shouldn't be null, but the test helps make dump()
4005 // more tolerant of malformed IR
4006 if (Operand && Operand->getType() != TheType) {
4007 PrintAllTypes = true; // We have differing types! Print them all!
4008 break;
4009 }
4010 }
4011 }
4012
4013 if (!PrintAllTypes) {
4014 Out << ' ';
4015 TypePrinter.print(TheType, Out);
4016 }
4017
4018 Out << ' ';
4019 for (unsigned i = 0, E = I.getNumOperands(); i != E; ++i) {
4020 if (i) Out << ", ";
4021 writeOperand(I.getOperand(i), PrintAllTypes);
4022 }
4023 }
4024
4025 // Print atomic ordering/alignment for memory operations
4026 if (const LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(&I)) {
4027 if (LI->isAtomic())
4028 writeAtomic(LI->getContext(), LI->getOrdering(), LI->getSyncScopeID());
4029 if (LI->getAlignment())
4030 Out << ", align " << LI->getAlignment();
4031 } else if (const StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(&I)) {
4032 if (SI->isAtomic())
4033 writeAtomic(SI->getContext(), SI->getOrdering(), SI->getSyncScopeID());
4034 if (SI->getAlignment())
4035 Out << ", align " << SI->getAlignment();
4036 } else if (const AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI = dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(&I)) {
4037 writeAtomicCmpXchg(CXI->getContext(), CXI->getSuccessOrdering(),
4038 CXI->getFailureOrdering(), CXI->getSyncScopeID());
4039 } else if (const AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(&I)) {
4040 writeAtomic(RMWI->getContext(), RMWI->getOrdering(),
4041 RMWI->getSyncScopeID());
4042 } else if (const FenceInst *FI = dyn_cast<FenceInst>(&I)) {
4043 writeAtomic(FI->getContext(), FI->getOrdering(), FI->getSyncScopeID());
4044 }
4045
4046 // Print Metadata info.
4047 SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>, 4> InstMD;
4048 I.getAllMetadata(InstMD);
4049 printMetadataAttachments(InstMD, ", ");
4050
4051 // Print a nice comment.
4052 printInfoComment(I);
4053}
4054
4055void AssemblyWriter::printMetadataAttachments(
4056 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>> &MDs,
4057 StringRef Separator) {
4058 if (MDs.empty())
4059 return;
4060
4061 if (MDNames.empty())
4062 MDs[0].second->getContext().getMDKindNames(MDNames);
4063
4064 for (const auto &I : MDs) {
4065 unsigned Kind = I.first;
4066 Out << Separator;
4067 if (Kind < MDNames.size()) {
4068 Out << "!";
4069 printMetadataIdentifier(MDNames[Kind], Out);
4070 } else
4071 Out << "!<unknown kind #" << Kind << ">";
4072 Out << ' ';
4073 WriteAsOperandInternal(Out, I.second, &TypePrinter, &Machine, TheModule);
4074 }
4075}

4080 Out << "\n";

4083void AssemblyWriter::writeAllMDNodes() {
4084 SmallVector<const MDNode *, 16> Nodes;
4085 Nodes.resize(Machine.mdn_size());
4086 for (SlotTracker::mdn_iterator I = Machine.mdn_begin(), E = Machine.mdn_end();
4087 I != E; ++I)
4088 Nodes[I->second] = cast<MDNode>(I->first);
4089
4090 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Nodes.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4091 writeMDNode(i, Nodes[i]);
4092 }
4093}

4099void AssemblyWriter::writeAllAttributeGroups() {
4100 std::vector<std::pair<AttributeSet, unsigned>> asVec;
4101 asVec.resize(Machine.as_size());
4102
4103 for (SlotTracker::as_iterator I = Machine.as_begin(), E = Machine.as_end();
4104 I != E; ++I)
4105 asVec[I->second] = *I;
4106
4107 for (const auto &I : asVec)
4108 Out << "attributes #" << I.second << " = { "
4109 << I.first.getAsString(true) << " }\n";
4110}

4112void AssemblyWriter::printUseListOrder(const UseListOrder &Order) {
4113 bool IsInFunction = Machine.getFunction();
4114 if (IsInFunction)
4115 Out << " ";
4116
4117 Out << "uselistorder";
4118 if (const BasicBlock *BB =
4119 IsInFunction ? nullptr : dyn_cast<BasicBlock>(Order.V)) {
4120 Out << "_bb ";
4121 writeOperand(BB->getParent(), false);
4122 Out << ", ";
4123 writeOperand(BB, false);
4124 } else {
4125 Out << " ";
4126 writeOperand(Order.V, true);
4127 }
4128 Out << ", { ";
4129
4130 assert(Order.Shuffle.size() >= 2 && "Shuffle too small");
4131 Out << Order.Shuffle[0];
4132 for (unsigned I = 1, E = Order.Shuffle.size(); I != E; ++I)
4133 Out << ", " << Order.Shuffle[I];
4134 Out << " }\n";
4135}
4136
4137void AssemblyWriter::printUseLists(const Function *F) {
4138 auto hasMore =
4139 [&]() { return !UseListOrders.empty() && UseListOrders.back().F == F; };
4140 if (!hasMore())
4141 // Nothing to do.
4142 return;
4143
4144 Out << "\n; uselistorder directives\n";
4145 while (hasMore()) {
4146 printUseListOrder(UseListOrders.back());
4147 UseListOrders.pop_back();
4148 }
4149}

4238static bool isReferencingMDNode(const Instruction &I) {
4239 if (const auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&I))
4240 if (Function *F = CI->getCalledFunction())
4241 if (F->isIntrinsic())
4242 for (auto &Op : I.operands())
4243 if (auto *V = dyn_cast_or_null<MetadataAsValue>(Op))
4244 if (isa<MDNode>(V->getMetadata()))
4245 return true;
4246 return false;
4247}

4249void Value::print(raw_ostream &ROS, bool IsForDebug) const {
4250 bool ShouldInitializeAllMetadata = false;
4251 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(this))
4252 ShouldInitializeAllMetadata = isReferencingMDNode(*I);
4253 else if (isa<Function>(this) || isa<MetadataAsValue>(this))
4254 ShouldInitializeAllMetadata = true;
4255
4256 ModuleSlotTracker MST(getModuleFromVal(this), ShouldInitializeAllMetadata);
4257 print(ROS, MST, IsForDebug);
4258}
4259
4260void Value::print(raw_ostream &ROS, ModuleSlotTracker &MST,
4261 bool IsForDebug) const {
4262 formatted_raw_ostream OS(ROS);
4263 SlotTracker EmptySlotTable(static_cast<const Module *>(nullptr));
4264 SlotTracker &SlotTable =
4265 MST.getMachine() ? *MST.getMachine() : EmptySlotTable;
4266 auto incorporateFunction = [&](const Function *F) {
4267 if (F)
4268 MST.incorporateFunction(*F);
4269 };
4270
4271 if (const Instruction *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(this)) {
4272 incorporateFunction(I->getParent() ? I->getParent()->getParent() : nullptr);
4273 AssemblyWriter W(OS, SlotTable, getModuleFromVal(I), nullptr, IsForDebug);
4274 W.printInstruction(*I);
4275 } else if (const BasicBlock *BB = dyn_cast<BasicBlock>(this)) {
4276 incorporateFunction(BB->getParent());
4277 AssemblyWriter W(OS, SlotTable, getModuleFromVal(BB), nullptr, IsForDebug);
4278 W.printBasicBlock(BB);
4279 } else if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(this)) {
4280 AssemblyWriter W(OS, SlotTable, GV->getParent(), nullptr, IsForDebug);
4281 if (const GlobalVariable *V = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GV))
4282 W.printGlobal(V);
4283 else if (const Function *F = dyn_cast<Function>(GV))
4284 W.printFunction(F);
4285 else
4286 W.printIndirectSymbol(cast<GlobalIndirectSymbol>(GV));
4287 } else if (const MetadataAsValue *V = dyn_cast<MetadataAsValue>(this)) {
4288 V->getMetadata()->print(ROS, MST, getModuleFromVal(V));
4289 } else if (const Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(this)) {
4290 TypePrinting TypePrinter;
4291 TypePrinter.print(C->getType(), OS);
4292 OS << ' ';
4293 WriteConstantInternal(OS, C, TypePrinter, MST.getMachine(), nullptr);
4294 } else if (isa<InlineAsm>(this) || isa<Argument>(this)) {
4295 this->printAsOperand(OS, /* PrintType */ true, MST);
4296 } else {
4297 llvm_unreachable("Unknown value to print out!");
4298 }
4299}

4301/// Print without a type, skipping the TypePrinting object.
4302///
4303/// \return \c true iff printing was successful.
4304static bool printWithoutType(const Value &V, raw_ostream &O,
4305 SlotTracker *Machine, const Module *M) {
4306 if (V.hasName() || isa<GlobalValue>(V) ||
4307 (!isa<Constant>(V) && !isa<MetadataAsValue>(V))) {
4308 WriteAsOperandInternal(O, &V, nullptr, Machine, M);
4309 return true;
4310 }
4311 return false;
4312}

4314static void printAsOperandImpl(const Value &V, raw_ostream &O, bool PrintType,
4315 ModuleSlotTracker &MST) {
4316 TypePrinting TypePrinter(MST.getModule());
4317 if (PrintType) {
4318 TypePrinter.print(V.getType(), O);
4319 O << ' ';
4320 }
4321
4322 WriteAsOperandInternal(O, &V, &TypePrinter, MST.getMachine(),
4323 MST.getModule());
4324}

4326void Value::printAsOperand(raw_ostream &O, bool PrintType,
4327 const Module *M) const {
4328 if (!M)
4329 M = getModuleFromVal(this);

4331 if (!PrintType)
4332 if (printWithoutType(*this, O, nullptr, M))
4333 return;
